    "summary": "I am a broadly interested ecologist with a diverse skill set which is also well applicable outside of ecology. My main strengths are in data analytics and managing projects, while I also have a strong track record in academic publishing.\n\nSome of my accomplishments:\n1) Managed three large research projects, involving >20 people, in the Netherlands, Denmark, and Brazil from start (research design) to end (publication). All projects involved writing proposals to receive funding, and collaborating with people from different organisations and cultural backgrounds.\n2) Three first-author peer-reviewed publications in renowned academic journals (Science of The Total Environment, Frontiers in Environmental Science, ISME Communications). Two more in review.\n3) Analysed several large datasets, including microbial datasets wth ~10 million records and camera trapping datasets of ~100.000 records.\n4) I can speak five languagues, of which two fluent (Dutch, English) and three conversational (German, Spanish, Portuguese).\n5) Supervised five master students, of which four are now PhD students.\n6) Love to travel and to work together with people from different cultural backgrounds.",
