                    "description": "PhD on methane emissions from shallow lakes and how they are regulated by the microbial community in the sediment.\n\uf0b7 Wrote research proposal for PhD from scratch.\n\uf0b7 Set up and carried out research projects in Brazil, Denmark and the Netherlands.\n\uf0b7 Analysed large datasets, including microbial community datasets of >10 million reads using dada2 and phyloseq.\n\uf0b7 Individual supervision of master internships and supervision of student groups in master courses.\n\uf0b7 Three publications, two publications in progress\n\uf0b7 Applied several field and laboratory methods, including:\n- greenhouse gas diffusive fluxes and ebullition\n- potential methane oxidation and production incubations\n- molecular analyses of microbial DNA (e.g. DNA extractions, qPCR)\n- surface and pore water analyses\n- soil/sediment analyses",
